############################ How to use #################################

Use axtor to get the kernel.cl
$axtor kernel.bc -o kernel.cl -m OCL

Note: The input file must be represented as the first argument according to
      the source code. The option "-m OCL" specifies the axtor to use the OpenCL
      backend.
      

########################## About axtor ##################################

The origin repo of axtor is at https://bitbucket.org/gnarf/axtor.git
In this directory contains its original README, LICENSE, TODO files.
